JOHANNESBURG - Polokwane City football club on Monday warned the public about a scam going around offering football trials in exchange for money on social media.The club issued the following statement on the matter:READ: Polokwane City snatch point against Highlands Park We recently received numerous calls about a guy who claims to be coach Bernard Molekwa on Facebook, promising trials in exchange for money."Polokwane City FC would like to state that coach Bernard Molekwa is not active on social media," the statement read. The club would like to distance itself from any trials alert going around on social media."The club's management advise people to contact the club directly for any information needed.African News Agency